properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 8 at 9:27PM CST until February 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...SNOW ON SUNDAY...

.Light to moderate snow will develop Sunday morning then diminish
late Sunday afternoon into the evening over northwest Wisconsin.
Snowfall from 2 inches to around 4 inches, with up to 5 inches
possible over the southern portion of Price County.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 5
inches.

* WHERE...Price County.

* WHEN...From 6 AM to 6 PM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO 6 PM CST SUNDAY
